      <div class="node">
        <h2 class="title"><a href="/alert/syndicated-sleep-column-newspapers">Syndicated Sleep Column for Newspapers</a></h2>    <span class="submitted"></span>
    <div class="taxonomy"></div>
    <div class="content"><table><tr><td>
<p>The National Sleep Foundation invites local newspapers to <a href="http://www.sleepfoundation.org/subscription">subscribe to a new syndicated column</a> on sleep health and safety.</p>
</td></tr></table></div>
    <div class="links"><ul class="links inline"><li class="node_read_more first last"><a href="/alert/syndicated-sleep-column-newspapers" title="Read the rest of Syndicated Sleep Column for Newspapers.">Read more</a></li>
</ul></div>  </div>
  </div>
  <div class="views-row views-row-4 views-row-even views-row-last">
      <div class="node">
        <h2 class="title"><a href="/alert/follow-sleep-health-safety-2011-conference-twitter">Follow Sleep Health &amp; Safety 2011 Conference  on Twitter</a></h2>    <span class="submitted"></span>
    <div class="taxonomy"></div>
    <div class="content"><table><tr><td>
<div class='alert-image'><img src='/sites/default/files/shs_alert.jpg'></div><p>The National Sleep Foundation Sleep Health &amp; Safety conference begins today, March 17, 2011 at the JW Marriott in Washington, DC. If you are unable to attend, you can <strong><a href="/sleep-health-safety-twitter">follow our Twitter feed</a></strong> for presentation re-caps, and feedback on abstracts being presented at the conference.</p>
</td></tr></table></div>
    <div class="links"><ul class="links inline"><li class="node_read_more first last"><a href="/alert/follow-sleep-health-safety-2011-conference-twitter" title="Read the rest of Follow Sleep Health &amp; Safety 2011 Conference  on Twitter.">Read more</a></li>
</ul></div>  </div>
